Let the width of the rectangle be $w$ meters and the radius of the semicircles be $r$ meters.

We are given that the length of the track is 400 meters.  Thus, we have

\begin{align*}
2(w + 2r) &= 400 \\
w + 2r &= 200 \\
\end{align*}

From the second equation, we have $w = 200 - 2r$.  Substituting this into the first equation, we have

\begin{align*}
2(200 - 2r + 2r) &= 400 \\
200 - 2r + 2r &= 400 \\
200 &= 400 \\
\end{align*}

This is a contradiction, so the given situation cannot occur.  The largest possible area of the field is $0$ square meters.

